label: City · Texas
name: Dallas
notes: Major metropolitan area in Texas and the site of the JFK assassination on November 22, 1963.

label: City · Louisiana
name: New Orleans
notes: Birthplace of Lee Harvey Oswald and a significant location for his activities in the summer of 1963.

label: City · Texas
name: Irving
notes: A suburb of Dallas where the Paine residence was located and where Lee Harvey Oswald spent the night before the assassination.

label: Public Square · Dallas
name: Dealey Plaza
notes: A city park in the West End district of downtown Dallas where President John F. Kennedy was assassinated.

label: Building · Dallas
name: Texas School Book Depository
notes: The workplace of Lee Harvey Oswald and the site from which the Warren Commission concluded he fired the shots that killed President Kennedy.

label: Private Residence · Dallas
name: Walker Residence (Turtle Creek)
notes: The home of General Edwin Walker at 4011 Turtle Creek Blvd, where an assassination attempt occurred on April 10, 1963.

label: Business · Dallas
name: Texas Butcher's Supply
notes: A business in Dallas where Ralph Leon Yates was employed and from where he purportedly picked up a hitchhiker matching Oswald's description.

label: Private Residence · Irving
name: Ruth Paine Residence (Irving)
notes: The home of Ruth and Michael Paine where Marina Oswald lived in late 1963 and where Lee Harvey Oswald kept his rifle.

label: Infrastructure · Dealey Plaza
name: Triple Underpass
notes: Railway overpass at the west end of Dealey Plaza where Elm, Main, and Commerce Streets converge. Mentioned by the Yates hitchhiker as he exited the vehicle.

label: Neighborhood · Dallas, TX
name: Oak Cliff
notes: Section of Dallas located south of downtown. Significant location for the activities of Lee Harvey Oswald in 1963.

label: Shopping Center · Dallas, TX
name: Wynnewood Village
notes: Shopping center in Oak Cliff section of Dallas. Location of Charlie's Ranch Meat Market.

label: Street · Irving, TX
name: Shady Grove Road at Story Road
notes: Location of Park-It Market Drive-In Grocery and destination of Yates' verified service call on November 21, 1963.

label: Private Residence · Dallas, TX
name: 13564 Brookgreen, Dallas TX
notes: The 1963 home of Ralph Leon Yates and his family.

label: Private Residence · Dallas, TX
name: 13770 Sprucewood, Dallas TX
notes: The residence of J.O. Smith, uncle of Ralph Leon Yates.

label: Private Residence · Oak Cliff
name: 1026 N. Beckley Avenue (Rooming House)
notes: Lee Harvey Oswald's rooming house in Oak Cliff. He returned here briefly after the assassination before walking to the scene of the Tippit shooting.

label: Federal Office · Dallas, TX
name: Dallas FBI Office
notes: FBI field office in Dallas, Texas. Location where Ralph Yates reported his sighting and was interviewed multiple times between November 1963 and January 1964.
